{"uid":"fe34f64877378674","name":"QA 1922","fullName":"QA #1922 on ubuntu2004-container","historyId":"1922@ubuntu2004-container","time":{"start":1782169615000,"stop":1782169616000,"duration":1000},"description":"PCP QA Test No. 1922\n\nExercise pmproxy REST API /series/values endpoint with negative\n\nrelative time offsets (e.g. start=-30s).  This is the end-to-end\n\nintegration test for the series/values time parsing fix\n\n(GitHub issue #2503).\n\n\n\nWithout the fix, pmproxy crashes or disconnects when it receives\n\na negative relative offset.  With the fix, it returns an empty\n\narray (the archive data is from 2017, so -30s finds nothing).\n\n\n\nCopyright (c) 2024 Red Hat.\n\n\n\n","descriptionHtml":"<p>PCP QA Test No. 1922</p>\n<p>Exercise pmproxy REST API /series/values endpoint with negative</p>\n<p>relative time offsets (e.g. start=-30s).  This is the end-to-end</p>\n<p>integration test for the series/values time parsing fix</p>\n<p>(GitHub issue #2503).</p>\n<p>Without the fix, pmproxy crashes or disconnects when it receives</p>\n<p>a negative relative offset.  With the fix, it returns an empty</p>\n<p>array (the archive data is from 2017, so -30s finds nothing).</p>\n<p>Copyright (c) 2024 Red Hat.</p>\n","status":"passed","statusMessage":"","flaky":false,"newFailed":false,"newBroken":false,"newPassed":false,"retriesCount":0,"retriesStatusChange":false,"beforeStages":[],"afterStages":[],"labels":[{"name":"suite","value":"ubuntu2004-container"},{"name":"host","value":"ubuntu2004-container"},{"name":"epic","value":"pmseries"},{"name":"epic","value":"pmproxy"},{"name":"epic","value":"libpcp_web"},{"name":"epic","value":"local"},{"name":"resultFormat","value":"allure2"}],"parameters":[],"links":[{"name":"Source","url":"https://github.com/performancecopilot/pcp/tree/e9bbdb8b938f3f2644fad5a21b2cee02faf790a4/qa/1922","type":"test_case"},{"name":"Expected output","url":"https://github.com/performancecopilot/pcp/tree/e9bbdb8b938f3f2644fad5a21b2cee02faf790a4/qa/1